    "This is especially important in critical application areas such as drug discovery and genetic diagnosis, where users not only need the accuracy of the model but also expect to be able to understand why the model makes the predictions it does.",
    "The non-interpretability of graph pooling methods makes it difficult for users to trust the output results of the model, thus hindering the application of graph pooling methods in these domains.",
    "Although numerous interpretable methods have emerged in the field of graph neural networks (Li et al. 2207 (Li et al., 2203;; Ying et al. 2019; Luo et al. 2020; Schlichtkrull et al. 2010; Wang et al. 2020c), interpretable research for the graph pooling process is still lacking.",
    "This is mainly due to the specificity of the graph pooling operation, which involves complex interactions between the topology of the graph and the node features, making it difficult to apply traditional interpretability techniques directly.",
    "The expressive power of graph pooling methods is highly dependent on the pooling methods adopted."
